==Description==

The [[Image:CAM_Array.svg|24px]] [[CAM_Array|CAM Array]] command creates a new path by duplicating another path several times at a certain interval distance.

==Usage==

# Select the operation you want to repeat
# Press the {{Button|[[Image:CAM_Array.svg|16px]] [[CAM_Array|Array]]}} button
# Press {{Button|Apply}}
# Adjust the desired properties at the data box

==Properties==

*{{PropertyData|Type}}: The array type: {{value|Linear1D}}, {{value|Linear2D}} or {{value|Polar}}
*{{PropertyData|Offset}}: The spacing between the array copies for each direction
*{{PropertyData|Copies}}: The number of copies (not counting the original) for each direction

{{Version|26.3}}: The previous percentage-based jitter control has been replaced by {{PropertyData|UseJitter}}. Jitter can be applied to polar arrays, and random rotation jitter is available for all array types.

*{{PropertyData|UseJitter}}: Enables random offsets and rotations for generated array copies
*{{PropertyData|JitterMagnitude}}: The maximum random translation in each direction
*{{PropertyData|JitterAngle}}: The maximum random rotation angle
*{{PropertyData|JitterSeed}}: The seed value for repeatable jitter

